-- Vekselberg's IES Is Biggest Russian Private Company by Sales, Forbes Says
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2010-09-27T05:06:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/vekselberg-s-ies-is-biggest-russian-private-company-by-sales-forbes-says.html
Billionaire Viktor Vekselberg ZAO
Integrated Energy Systems is Russia’s biggest private company by
revenue, which reached 264 billion rubles ($8.6 billion) last
year, according to Forbes magazine’s local edition.  IES replaced United Co. Rusal on the annual list, after the
aluminum company held an initial public offering in Hong Kong in
January, the magazine said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
